<P>
UNIVERSITY PROGRAM TO USE LOCAL SITE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LAURA PITTER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Students working toward master's degrees through UC Santa Barbara's off-campus 
studies department will no longer go to the Point Mugu Navy base for classes 
but will use the school's Ventura Center beginning in the fall. 
</P>
<P>
Graduate programs have been offered at Point Magu in computer science and 
electrical and computer engineering. Space became available in the Ventura 
Center at 3585 Maple St. about two years ago, when classes from Cal State 
Northridge were moved to their own facility. 
</P>
<P>
The graduate program could not move earlier because it had a yearlong contract 
with the Navy, student affairs officer Judy Cotton said. 
</P>
<P>
The program is geared toward re-entry students with an average age of about 35, 
Cotton said. LAURA PITTER 
</P>
