<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: SIMI VALLEY; 
</P>
<P>
PTA COUNCIL CHOSEN BEST IN THE STATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT LAWRENCE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Simi Valley PTA Council has been honored by the California State PTA as the 
most outstanding in the state for the 1989-90 academic year. 
</P>
<P>
Council President Janice DiFatta said she and the council's 20 board members 
were "beside themselves" after learning they had been selected from about 200 
councils statewide. 
</P>
<P>
"It's really an honor to have been considered for the award and then to receive 
it," DiFatta said. 
</P>
<P>
The council has about 10,000 members in 24 units. DiFatta said her organization 
caught the attention of the judges with a wide menu of policies and programs. 
The council created a program to educate parents about substance abuse, work 
habits, teen-age pregnancy and suicide. 
</P>
<P>
The council also devised an incentive scheme where points are awarded to PTA 
units based on the number of activities and projects undertaken, reports put 
out, and attendance at Simi Valley Council and district meetings. 
</P>
<P>
The Simi Valley PTA Council was also the state's most outstanding in 1983. 
SCOTT LAWRENCE 
</P>
</TEXT>
