<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: UNIHEALTH MIGHT PURCHASE MORE PACIFICARE SHARES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UniHealth America, a Burbank-based nonprofit concern that owns hospitals and 
other health care organizations, said it might purchase up to 500,000 
additional shares of PacifiCare Health Systems Inc., a Cypress-based health 
maintenance organization. 
</P>
<P>
The purchase would raise UniHealth's stake in PacifiCare from 58% to 62% of the 
total shares outstanding. However, that percentage could be affected by 
PacifiCare's announcement last week that it might repurchase up to 500,000 
shares of its common stock. 
</P>
<P>
UniHealth said the stock purchase would be coordinated with PacifiCare's, and 
would be made "when business conditions are favorable." 
</P>
