<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: POP/ROCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
What a Boss: Bruce Springsteen has given $10,000 to singer Mary Wells, who is 
suffering from throat cancer and is broke. 
</P>
<P>
The money was donated in care of the Rhythm and Blues Foundation in Washington, 
a non-profit group that comes to the aid of blues singers. Singer Bonnie Raitt 
has also pitched in to help Wells, the former Motown star known for the 1964 
song "My Guy." Wells, 47, is receiving outpatient radiation treatments at 
County-USC Medical Center, has no health insurance and has been evicted from 
her Los Angeles apartment. BETH KLEID 
