<P>
A Horse Is a Horse: About 200 people milled around Sunday under a wild cherry 
tree in Tahlequah, Okla., where Mr. Ed, the 1960s television star, is said to 
be buried. 
</P>
<P>
But there's no record of his death because Mr. Ed was a horse, of course. A 
5-foot granite monument, with a picture of the "talking horse" sticking his 
head out over a barn door, was unveiled on the farm of Danny and Darlene 
Snodgrass. In another version of Mr. Ed's demise, a person associated with the 
show said the horse died in 1973 and was cremated, and his ashes strewn over 
Hollywood. BETH KLEID 
