<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 1 KILLED, 2 WOUNDED IN SUSPECTED GANG 
SHOOTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
One man was killed and two youths were wounded early Monday as they left a 
South Los Angeles home in what police believe was a gang-related shooting, 
sheriff's deputies said. 
</P>
<P>
Police said all three victims -- who are believed to be gang members -- were 
leaving a house in the 8700 block of Fir Avenue at 4:30 a.m. when a rival gang 
member opened fire. 
</P>
<P>
A 25-year-old was shot twice in the chest and died at the scene. His name had 
not been released late Monday, pending notification of relatives. 
</P>
<P>
The other two victims, both juveniles, were also shot in the chest. They were 
taken to Martin Luther King Jr./Drew Medical Center, where one was in critical 
condition and the other in stable condition Monday afternoon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
