<P>
T-Bill Rates Mixed: The Treasury sold $9.2 billion of new three-month bills at 
an average discount rate of 7.49%, down from 7.55% last week. Another $9.2 
billion of new six-month bills was sold at an average discount rate of 7.48%, 
up from 7.45% last week. 
</P>
<P>
The rates were the lowest for three-month bills since they sold for 7.41% on 
Aug. 13. It was the highest for six-month bills since they averaged 7.52% on 
July 16. The new discount rates understate the actual return to investors: 
7.74% for three-month bills, with a $10,000 bill selling for $9,810.70, and 
7.88% for a six-month bill selling for $9,621.80. The discount rate reflects 
the price discount received when government securities are purchased at less 
than face value. 
</P>
