</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jeffrey A. Perlman and Steve Emmons 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAKING TRACKS: But some like to ride the rails, even if they don't like to be 
taxed for it. . . . Ridership on Orange County's new commuter trains along I-5 
between San Juan Capistrano and Los Angeles has soared 20% since May to 337 a 
day. Still, that's far short of the trains' 1,200-seat round-trip capacity, so 
monthly fares, already 20% below Amtrak rates, will fall another 10%. Also, a 
direct mail marketing effort is in the works. Jeffrey A. Perlman and Steve 
Emmons 
