<P>
Foothill Thrift Verdict: A Superior Court jury awarded $564,000 to a defunct 
video surveillance firm that had alleged that Foothill Thrift &amp; Loan in Los 
Angeles improperly cut off its line of credit and liquidated the firm when it 
was losing money in 1985. Foothill had extended a line of credit of about $8 
million to Videoscope Inc., which sold its equipment to such customers as 
convenience stores, banks and hotels. Plaintiffs in the case had originally 
sought $11.5 million from Foothill. 
