<P>
SHOOTINGS STRIKE YOUNG VICTIMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A young boy sitting on his bicycle was shot and killed in an unexplained 
attack, and a 12-year-old girl described by police as a "gang wanna-be" was 
critically wounded in another shooting, authorities said today. 
</P>
<P>
The boy, Emiliano Landa, was hit once in the upper torso by shots fired at him 
and several of his friends Monday night in Norwalk. 
</P>
<P>
He was pronounced dead on arrival at Pioneer Hospital in Artesia, sheriff's 
deputies said. 
</P>
<P>
The girl, whom police declined to identify, was shot in the head and chest by 
two gang members on foot who opened fire on her and two boys about 4 p.m. 
Monday as they stood near the corner of Vermont Avenue and Olympic Boulevard, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
The girl was in critical condition and on life-support systems at Childrens 
Hospital. 
</P>
