</P>
<P>
E. GERMAN CITY EMPLOYEES STRIKE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
EAST BERLIN 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
About 45,000 municipal workers in at least 10 East German cities walked off 
their jobs for a few hours today in warning strikes for better wages and job 
security in a united Germany. 
</P>
<P>
Nurses, secretaries, bus drivers, garbage haulers and others stopped working 
for up to two hours, and demonstrations and rallies were held in a number of 
cities. There are about 1.6 million municipal workers in East Germany. 
</P>
<P>
The workers are demanding job protection and pay increases to compensate for 
higher prices that have resulted from the economic merger of the two Germanys 
on July 1. They also demand that East German income taxes not be immediately 
raised to West German levels. 
</P>
</TEXT>
